# Live tuning overlay layout

The focus-driven tree panel ([cleave/viz/overlay.py](cleave/viz/overlay.py), [cleave/viz/controls.py](cleave/viz/controls.py)) splits into two vertical sections. Use these names in docs, issues, and UI work.

## Track rows section

The upper block: all rows where `index < track_row_count(state)` (`track_row_count` sums non-footer rows from `build_row_layout`).

- One **track block** per stem in `layer_z_order`.
- **Base rows** (always present per stem): header, preset dir, preset, blend, opacity, beat sensitivity, then **cleave effects** header (`RowKind.TRACK_EFFECTS_HEADER`).
- **Effect sub-rows** (`RowKind.TRACK_EFFECT`): one per entry in [cleave/effects/registry.py](cleave/effects/registry.py) for that stem; visible only when both the track block and `TrackBlock.effects_expanded` are expanded.
- Per-stem state: `TrackBlock` in `TuningViewState.tracks` (`effects`, `effects_expanded`, plus preset/blend/opacity/beat fields).
- On-screen header label: `Layer N: STEM` (user-facing "layer"; code often says "track").
- **cleave effects** header: lowercase label `└─ cleave effects` plus expand arrow; collapsed by default; sits after beat sensitivity; Left/Right toggles `effects_expanded`.

Say **track rows section** for the whole upper block; **track row** for a single line.

After the four stem blocks, a blank **render section gap** row (`RowKind.RENDER_SECTION_GAP`) separates stems from render blocks. Then **Render: OVERLAY** (`RowKind.RENDER_OVERLAY_HEADER`) is always present. It is not reorderable (Enter does not enter move mode). Header label: `Render:` in `LABEL`, `OVERLAY` and expand arrow in value color. Sub-rows when expanded: position, opacity, border width, start delay, display time, title (expandable; font, font size, and margin-bottom sub-rows when expanded), body (expandable; font and font size sub-rows when expanded). State: `RenderOverlayBlock` / `RenderOverlayRuntime` on session; solo via `render_overlay_solo` (no audio impact). Disable clears solo and collapses.

Below overlay, **Render: POST FX** (`RowKind.RENDER_POST_FX_HEADER`) is always present. Same eye / expand / solo semantics as overlay (`render_post_fx_solo`; solo is not persisted). Sub-rows when expanded: fade in, fade out (seconds). State: `RenderPostFxBlock` / `RenderPostFxRuntime` on session. Disable clears solo and collapses.

Below post-FX, **Render: TIMELINE** (`RowKind.RENDER_TIMELINE_HEADER`) is always present. Eye / expand semantics match post-FX (no solo in v1). **Ctrl+Right** / **Ctrl+Left** toggles `session.timeline.enabled`; **Right** / **Left** toggles `session.timeline.expanded`. Disable collapses expanded. State: `RenderTimelineBlock` / `TimelineRuntime` on session. `enabled` persists via config snapshot; `expanded` is UI-only. No sub-rows in v1 (expand arrow is cosmetic). Press **t** in the main panel to open the timeline strip when enabled (toast if disabled).

## Timeline panel

Separate bottom overlay ([cleave/viz/timeline_overlay.py](cleave/viz/timeline_overlay.py), [cleave/viz/timeline_controls.py](cleave/viz/timeline_controls.py)). Open with **t** when `timeline.enabled`; **t** or **Esc** closes. While open, keyboard routes to timeline controls (main tree inactive). Rows follow `layer_z_order`; labels use stem abbreviations (D/B/V/O). Each row shows a monitor eye beside the label, the cue bar, and a committed-timeline eye at the far right: **left** = monitor/output (`effective_layer_enabled`; gold `OVERRIDE_BG` when stem is in `TimelineRuntime.override_stems`), **right** = committed cues at playhead only (`timeline_committed_visible`; updates on seek while paused preview leaves left eye on `TimelineRuntime.monitor`). **Enter** arms a row (`ARMED_BG` red fill, distinct from override eye). **Space** pause snapshots current output into `monitor` and sets `preview_active`; resume clears both. Num keys **1**-**4** toggle layer visibility while paused (preview via `monitor` or override via `override_visible`; adds stem to override when needed), write record buffer when recording (armed only), toggle `override_visible` while playing for stems in `override_stems` only. **Shift+Enter** toggles override on the focused row while playing or paused (manual override via `override_stems` / `override_visible`; clears preview on enter; distinct from main-panel `session.solo_stem`; ignored when recording). **Ctrl+Enter** toggles focused armed row at playhead during record only. Timeline strip does not use **Shift+Left** / **Shift+Right** for solo (transport seek). **r** start clears override, WYSIWYG-seeds `record_buffer` from current output vs committed for armed stems, clears preview, unpauses if needed; stop punch-overwrites armed range. `preview_active` / `monitor` / `override_stems` / `override_visible` are session-only on `TimelineRuntime`. Cue list persists under root `timeline:` in YAML (written last in snapshots). See [docs/timeline-idea.md](docs/timeline-idea.md).

## Footer rows section

The lower block after a visual gap (`footer_gap` in `draw()`): `footer_row_count(state)` rows (3).

- Row kinds: `RowKind.TRANSPORT`, `RowKind.CONFIG_HEADER` (non-navigable active config path), `SAVE_CONFIG`.
- Constant: `FOOTER_ROWS` (3); index via `footer_index = index - track_row_count(state)`.
- Enter on `SAVE_CONFIG` opens an `OVERWRITE` / `SAVE AS NEW` picker when overwrite is allowed (`allow_overwrite`; false for repo-root `cleave-viz-default.yaml`). Otherwise save-as-new runs immediately. Overwrite still uses the yes/no confirm dialog.

## Whole panel

`TuningOverlay` draws one panel (`panel_rect`). There are no separate section rectangles; layout is positional from the track-rows / footer-rows split.

## Typography roles

Colors live in [cleave/viz/theme.py](cleave/viz/theme.py). Label truncation uses [cleave/viz/text_fit.py](cleave/viz/text_fit.py). Row drawing uses `_row_value_color` and `_render_label_value_row`.

| Role | Constant | RGB | Use |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Label | `LABEL` | `(170, 210, 255)` | Light blue prefixes and section titles |
| Value | `VALUE` | `(255, 255, 255)` | Default white for values and state indicators |
| Disabled | `DISABLED` | `(140, 140, 140)` | Inactive rows and controls |
| Locked | `LOCKED` | `(235, 150, 150)` | Locked sub-rows that cannot be edited |

**Label + value rows** (`_render_label_value_row`): prefix in `LABEL`, value in the row value color. Applies to blend, opacity, beat, effect depth rows, cleave effects header (label + expand arrow), and track headers (`Layer N:` in `LABEL`; stem name and expand arrow in row value color).

**Expand arrows** (`▶` / `▼`): value role, not label. Drawn in the row value color (typically `VALUE`; follows focus, disabled, and locked state like other values).

**Visibility eye** (track, render overlay, render post-FX, and render timeline headers): `VALUE` when enabled, `DISABLED` when off. When soloed (`solo_stem` for main-panel stems, `render_overlay_solo` / `render_post_fx_solo` for render blocks; neither persisted), the eye stays white on `SOLO_BG`. **Shift + Right** enters solo; **Shift + Left** exits solo for the focused header. **Render: TIMELINE** header has no solo; the timeline strip uses **Shift+Enter** on the focused row for override (`override_stems` on `TimelineRuntime`; left eye `OVERRIDE_BG`). Timeline strip eyes use the same icon helper ([render_visibility_icon](cleave/viz/overlay.py)).

### Accent colors (not label/value roles)

| Constant | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `HIGHLIGHT` | Focused row text and background tint |
| `MOVE_MODE` | Z-order move mode text and background tint |
| `LOCK_ICON` | Red padlock glyph on locked track headers |
| `SOLO_BG` | Solid red background behind the visibility eye when that stem is soloed |
| `OVERRIDE_BG` | Solid gold background behind the timeline monitor eye when that stem is in override |
| `ARMED_BG` | Solid red row background on armed timeline rows |
| `PRESET_ICON` / `PRESET_FILE_ICON` | Folder and file glyphs on preset rows |

### Intentional exceptions

These rows do not split label and value; the implementation is deliberate:

- **Active config path** (`CONFIG_HEADER`): entire row drawn in `LABEL`.
- **Preset dir / preset filename**: single-color row text plus Material Icons (icon colors above).
- **Transport, save**: single-color footer rows in row value color. Save row uses `DISABLED` while `solo_active` (Enter blocked in controls).
- **Toasts**: `DISABLED`.
- **Confirm dialog** ([cleave/viz/confirm.py](cleave/viz/confirm.py)): message in `VALUE`; yes/no use `HIGHLIGHT` or `DISABLED` by focus.
- **Save choice dialog**: `OVERWRITE` / `SAVE AS NEW` options use the same highlight pattern as confirm yes/no.

When focus, move mode, disabled layer, locked sub-row, or empty preset applies, `_row_value_color` may return an accent or state color instead of `VALUE`. That override is expected.
